WorldStage Newsonline–  Juli Plc, a Nigerian quoted firm that is into  sale of Pharmaceutical and household consumer goods and production and marketing of Table and Sachet water – Juli Life Water has further released more outstanding financial statements as at 31st December 2017, 31st December 2018 and 31st December 2019 with turnover of N489,520,044; N474,832,488 and  N349,308,725 respectively. The result released at the Nigerian Stock Exchange showed that loss after taxation during the period stood at N34,879,118, N5,910,068 and N1,569,264 respectively. WorldStage on Tuesday reported that Juli Plc simultaneously released its financial statements as at 31st December 2015 and 31st December 2016 with turnover rise by 16% to N191,677,220  from N165,478,026 in 2015.